pc|ST|pc|D9|pc|D8|pc|S8|nt|hondo717: ok, let us talk about how to bid when pard opens 2@C.  Typically, these days you almost always bid 2@D over 2 clubs.  That can either be negative or "waiting." You only bid a suit if you have a 5+ card suit with 2 of the top 3 honors and 8+ points.  Bids of 2@H, 2@S, 3@C, and 3@D all show 5+ cards with AQ, AK, KQ or AKQ.  In this case dot would normally bid 2@D.  You could make a case for her to bid 2@H, since her suit is quite good, but she does not have 2 of top 3 honors.

Now, let us assume dot bid 2@D, when East bids 2N, the auction reverts to being the same as if East opened 2N in the first place. Here, West  would bid 3@D transfer (or 4@D if you play Texas transfer), and East would bid 3H (or 4H.) 3@C over 2N, would be Stayman. 
